instructionsAtSite:
Please be aware:
â¢ You must return for your second dose of the vaccine in 21 days (Pfizer) or 28 days (Moderna), this will be scheduled when you arrive for your first dose
â¢ You must be monitored for at least 15 minutes post-vaccine administration (you will not be able to leave until this has been completed)
â¢ Masks are required at all times
â¢ Do not arrive for an appointment if you have any COVID-like symptoms (fever, cough, GI upset) or were recently exposed to someone with COVID-19 in the past 14 days
â¢ If you have tested positive for COVID-19, please to not schedule an appointment until at least 14 days past completion of your quarantine period.
â¢ For the safety of all, Please do not bring children/family members with you to the appointment. One person may accompany those who need assistance.

You understand that you must bring the following to you vaccination appointment in order to be vaccinated:
â¢ Legal Photo ID
â¢ Insurance Card if you have Insurance
â¢ Verification of status as belonging to one of the above eligible groups (ie- work badge, paystub, letter from employer, ID with date of birth for those over 65)

Continue taking safety measures
While you wait for your COVID-19 vaccination - and even after you get your vaccine - please continue to protect yourself and others with the safety measures you have been taking. Continue to wear a mask, stay at least six feet away from people outside your household, and clean your hands often.
